---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Hallucination Detection - JZ Stafura"
  description="Active research into AI-hallucinated citations: when fabrication happens, in which fields, and where in a paper. Pipeline study using CrossRef verification and GPTZero scoring."
>
  <div class="back"><a href="/lab/">&#x2190; Lab</a></div>

  <section class="hero">
    <p class="overline">Lab / Active Research</p>
    <h1>Hallucination Detection</h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">When and why does AI-assisted writing fabricate citations in submitted and accepted academic papers?</p>
    <div class="meta-row">
      <span class="status status-research">Active Research</span>
      <div class="links">
        <a href="https://jzstafura-lab.github.io/hallucitation-detection/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Project Site &#x2197;</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/JZStafura-Lab/hallucitation-detection" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub &#x2197;</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="rqs">
    <h2>Research Questions</h2>
    <div class="rq-grid">
      <div class="rq">
        <span class="rq-label">RQ1 &mdash; Expertise</span>
        <p>Are hallucinated citations more likely when an author cites outside their primary domain of expertise?</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rq">
        <span class="rq-label">RQ2 &mdash; Domain Velocity</span>
        <p>Do fields with faster publication cycles produce higher hallucination rates than slower-moving fields?</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rq">
        <span class="rq-label">RQ3 &mdash; Location</span>
        <p>Do hallucinated citations cluster in particular sections of a paper (Related Work vs. Methods vs. Discussion)?</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pipeline">
    <h2>Pipeline</h2>
    <p>The project uses a four-phase automated and semi-automated pipeline targeting a stratified random sample of ~300&ndash;400 papers across fields with differing publication velocities.</p>
    <div class="phases">
      <div class="phase">
        <span class="phase-num">0</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Collection</strong>
          <p>Stratified sampling and PDF acquisition across target venues. Semi-automated with seeded random sampling for reproducibility.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="phase">
        <span class="phase-num">1</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Extraction</strong>
          <p>Citation extraction from PDFs; CrossRef verification; GPTZero AI-content scoring. Fully automated.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="phase">
        <span class="phase-num">2</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Coding</strong>
          <p>Manual coding of author expertise and citation characteristics via an interactive interface. ~20 min/paper.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="phase">
        <span class="phase-num">3</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Analysis</strong>
          <p>Hypothesis testing and visualization. Logistic regression on citation-level data; mixed models accounting for paper-level clustering.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Stack</h2>
    <div class="tags">
      <span>Python</span>
      <span>CrossRef API</span>
      <span>GPTZero API</span>
      <span>Quarto</span>
      <span>Statistical Analysis</span>
      <span>PDF Extraction</span>
    </div>
    <p class="note">Pre-print forthcoming. Citation details will be added upon publication.</p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .back { padding: 1.5rem 0 0; }
  .back a { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--color-muted); }
  .back a:hover { color: var(--color-accent); }
  .overline { font-size: 0.75rem; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--color-muted); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .hero { padding: 2.5rem 0 2rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
  .hero h1 { font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.75rem); font-weight: normal; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .hero-sub { max-width: 55ch; color: var(--color-muted); margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
  .meta-row { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1.5rem; }
  .status { font-size: 0.65rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; padding: 0.2rem 0.55rem; border: 1px solid; }
  .status-research { color: #d97706; border-color: rgba(217, 119, 6, 0.3); background: rgba(217, 119, 6, 0.05); }
  .links { display: flex; gap: 1.25rem; }
  .links a { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--color-muted); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); padding-bottom: 1px; }
  .links a:hover { color: var(--color-accent); text-decoration: none; }
  section { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
  h2 { font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: 0.02em; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
  .rq-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(240px, 1fr)); gap: 1.5rem; }
  .rq { padding: 1.5rem; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .rq-label { font-size: 0.7rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--color-accent); display: block; margin-bottom: 0.6rem; }
  .rq p { font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-muted); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0; }
  .pipeline p { color: var(--color-muted); font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.7; max-width: 60ch; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .phases { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .phase { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 3rem 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); align-items: start; }
  .phase:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .phase-num { font-size: 1.5rem; color: var(--color-border); font-family: var(--font-mono); line-height: 1.4; }
  .phase strong { display: block; font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
  .phase p { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--color-muted); margin: 0; line-height: 1.6; }
  .tags { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.4rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .tags span { font-size: 0.65rem; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--color-muted); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem; }
  .note { font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--color-muted); font-style: italic; }
</style>
